1. Table Design with Correct Data Types & Constraints


SQL Script â€“ Table Creation
CREATE DATABASE  intern_training_db;
USE intern_training_db;

CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    last_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    date_of_birth DATE NOT NULL,
    gender CHAR(1),
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);


2. Explanation of Constraints (Documentation)
Constraint	Purpose
PRIMARY KEY-	Uniquely identifies each student
AUTO_INCREMENT-	Automatically generates student IDs
NOT NULL	-Prevents missing essential data
UNIQUE	-Prevents duplicate email records
DEFAULT	-Automatically assigns timestamp
